person:biography.personal-details:content: MD, PhD in Nephrology. Formerly: Resident of internal medicine and nephrology (1975-1977), professor of internal medicine from propaedeutics division (1979-1986), physician intensive care and nephrologist in the intensive care unit at the Hospital Israelita Albert Einstein (1976-2000), co-founder of Department of Health Informatics where it works since 1987, director of the IT department (2003-2008), dean of administration (2008-2009) and IT director of Hospital São Paulo (2009-2010). Author and patent holder of the decision support system in nutrition - NutWin and led the creation of the electronic medical record for the outpatients (2007). Currently: Full Professor from Department of Health Informatics at the Escola Paulista de Medicina from the Federal University of Sao Paulo. Meide Anção lives and resides in the city of Sao Paulo, Brazil
